-- CarVal Appoints Belonogoff, Graf as Senior Managing Directors
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2012-08-28T13:59:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/carval-appoints-belonogoff-graf-as-senior-managing-directors.html
CarVal Investors LLC,  an asset
manager owned by Cargill Inc., said it appointed Greg Belonogoff
and Joe Graf as senior managing directors.  Belonogoff, who began his career with CarVal in 1998,
manages the Minneapolis-based firm’s corporate securities
investments in the U.K.,  Europe  and Scandinavia from  London ,
focusing on restructurings and liquidations, according to an e-
mailed statement.  Graf, based in New York, manages CarVal’s  emerging markets 
credit business. He joined CarVal from Credit Suisse Group AG in
2006.  The firm’s CVI Credit Value Fund generated 16.3 percent of
net returns in the first seven months of the year. The CVI
Global Value Fund I and CVI Global Value Fund II charted 10.9
percent and 10.3 percent returns, according to CarVal, which
manages more than $9 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
